      "message": "The RVA isn’t the index I was talking about (and nothing in the structure prevents two streams from pointing to the same RVA). What I meant was: each stream appears in the minidump’s stream directory in a specific sequence. State the index into stream_directory_ here.\n\nThat would mean iterating over stream_directory_ instead of stream_map_, but this should be fine because you’re not actually trying to address a single stream by its type, you’re collecting a bunch of streams. Actually, walking the full suite of streams in a minidump by stream_directory_ is probably more efficient than using stream_map_.",
